cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about achieving state-of-the-art accuracy in object detection while minimizing computational cost, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the design of the neural network, which involves techniques such as batch normalization and residual connections, indicating that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of learning rate scheduling and hyperparameters, which are common topics in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of concatenated ReLU and Inception blocks suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper presents results on object detection benchmarks, indicating that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
